section.def:
member
                (海關人員) means a person holding an office specified
            in the Schedule 1;

paragraph.content:
the provisions of Public Service (Administration) Order and government
                regulations which relate to interdiction and the payment of emoluments thereafter
                shall apply;

if a senior officer, in accordance with Public Service (Administration)
                    Order and government regulations; (Amended 76 of 1999 s.
                            3)

if a senior officer, in accordance with Public Service (Administration)
                    Order and government regulations; (Amended 76 of 1999 s.
                            3)

the punishment of a subordinate officer for any disciplinary offence or
                    where he is found guilty of or pleads guilty to a criminal offence as defined in
                        section 14(2);

during the prevention, suppression or
                                                  investigation of an offence endangering national
                                                  security;

section.def:
acquire
                (取得) means acquire by purchase or by any other
            lawful means;

paragraph.content:
facilities that are not chargeable to the general revenue, including
                    holiday premises and recreational facilities (whether provided free or for a
                    charge);

social, educational and recreational activities and performances (whether
                    provided free or for a charge and whether provided for participation or as
                    spectator events);

section.def:
corporation
                (法團) means the corporation sole constituted under
                section 19(1);

paragraph.content:
whose contract of service as a member of the Service has expired on or
                    after the person reached 55 years of age without the contract being
                    renewed;

section.def:
function
                (職能) includes a power, an authority and a
            duty;

Fund
                (基金) means the Customs and Excise Service Welfare
            Fund continued by section 19A;

paragraph.content:
all fees collected from social, educational and recreational activities
                organized by or on behalf of the Commissioner for the purposes of the
                Fund;

granting financial assistance to dependants of deceased members and
                    deceased former members of the Service in order to meet the funeral expenses of
                    those deceased members and deceased former members;

if a Customs and Excise Staff Purchase Scheme is established under
                        section 19E, undertaking transactions for the purpose of giving
                    effect to the Scheme;
